1 AN ACT relating to interpreters.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 ïƒ¢Section 1. KRS 309.312 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) To be eligible for licensure by the board as an interpreter, the applicant shall submit
5 an application which includes:
6 (a) An application fee; and
7 (b) Current certification from a nationally recognized organization at the requisite
8 level for sign language interpreters, oral interpreters, or cued speech
9 transliterators as determined by the board and promulgated by administrative
10 regulation.
11 (2) The board shall issue an interpreter license to an applicant who fulfills these
12 requirements. The front of the license shall clearly list all certifications held by the
13 licensee.
14 (3) The board may issue a temporary license as an interpreter to an applicant who is
15 certified at a level below that required for licensure in subsection (1) of this section.
16 A temporary license shall be available for a person who is training under the
17 supervision of a licensed interpreter under circumstances defined by the board in
18 administrative regulation. A temporary license is valid for only a certain period
19 until the licensee achieves the minimum level of certification required for licensure
20 under subsection (1) of this section. A temporary license is not renewable although
21 extensions may be granted under circumstances defined by administrative
22 regulation.
23 (a) For graduates of a baccalaureate interpreter training program, a temporary
24 license shall be valid for up to one (1) year.
25 (b) For graduates of an associate of arts interpreter training program, a temporary
26 license shall be valid for up to two (2) years.
27 (c) For nondegree applicants, a temporary license shall be valid for up to two (2)
